      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold first {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the yolk of the {{eggs}} and the {{water}}. Wrap and chill an hour. Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll, line a 23 cm tart tin, trim, prick. Blind-bake with baking beans for 15 minutes; remove beans and bake another 8 minutes until pale gold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Apple compote",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the {{apple-bramley}} with the {{caster-sugar}}, juice of the {{lemon}} and the second {{unsalted-butter}} in a covered saucepan over a low heat for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring once or twice; the apples should collapse to a smooth compote. Take off the heat and cool slightly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Compote in, ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "apple fan",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99deqv00009sv4kxuzyorl"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", glaze",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the warm compote into the pastry shell. Slice the {{apple-eating}} into 3 mm slices and arrange in overlapping concentric circles from the rim inward. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes; the apple slices should be tender and slightly burnished at the edges. Warm the {{apricot-jam}} with 1 tablespoon of water and strain through a sieve. Brush the warm glaze generously over the apples. Cool to room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
